</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1196,1544]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1375,1400]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Comments.</emphasis>
We have found similar leaf mines in 
<collectingRegion box="[759,815,1376,1399]" country="United States of America" name="Iowa" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Iowa</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[871,930,1375,1400]" country="United States of America" name="Ohio" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Ohio</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[942,1114,1375,1400]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="ref103273" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1969) The Agromyzidae of Canada and Alaska. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 64, 1 - 311. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 10164 fv" type="journal article">Spencer (1969)</bibRefCitation>
reported what was probably the same mine on 
<emphasis box="[378,642,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Campanula 
<taxonomicName box="[522,642,1413,1436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vicia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="americana">americana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[689,777,1412,1437]" country="Canada" name="Ontario" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Ontario</collectingRegion>
, the only difference being that there were short lateral offshoots from the midrib into the leaf blade. He obtained 
<taxonomicName box="[830,944,1449,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Liriomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[830,944,1449,1472]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Liriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
puparia from these but was unable to rear adults. Apart from our single poor female specimen, no 
<collectingRegion box="[849,914,1484,1509]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">North</collectingRegion>
American leafminer has been reared from 
<emphasis box="[151,282,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Campanula</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
